---
layout: layouts/base-finpay.njk
title: "TSP Mutual Fund Window Management | Federal Employee Benefits Advisor"
description: "Expert management of your TSP Mutual Fund Window. Access 5,000+ funds beyond G, F, C, S, I with fiduciary guidance. Capital Wealth, Lehi, Utah."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "Federal Benefits", url: "/services/federal-benefits/" }
  - { name: "TSP Mutual Fund Window", url: "/services/federal-benefits/tsp-mutual-fund-window/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "How do I open the TSP Mutual Fund Window?"
    answer: "Log into your TSP account at tsp.gov, navigate to 'Mutual Fund Window,' and follow the enrollment steps. You'll need a minimum TSP balance. Capital Wealth can walk you through the process."
  - question: "What funds are available?"
    answer: "Over 5,000 mutual funds from major providers including Fidelity, Vanguard, T. Rowe Price, American Funds, PIMCO, and many others. Individual stocks and ETFs are not available — only mutual funds."
  - question: "Should I move all my TSP money to the Window?"
    answer: "Almost certainly not. The core TSP funds (especially C, S, and I) have rock-bottom expense ratios. The best strategy usually combines core TSP funds with targeted Mutual Fund Window selections for asset classes the core doesn't cover."
  - question: "What are the fees?"
    answer: "You'll pay a $28.75 annual maintenance fee, plus the expense ratios of whatever mutual funds you select (these vary from 0.03% to over 1%). There may also be per-trade fees. We ensure your total costs are justified by the added diversification."
  - question: "Can I move money back to core TSP?"
    answer: "Yes. You can transfer money between the Mutual Fund Window and your core TSP allocation. There are no penalties for moving back."
